    <button class="accordion">Tasks</button>
    <div class="panel">
        <p>This is an application that acts as a very simplistic booking system. Within the system you have the ability to manage guests, hotels and bookings.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Write an application that takes in a string of JSON containing an array of objects each with a date and rate pair. <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle completed"></span>
                <ul>
                    <li>The user has an option of inserting JSON into a textfield and then uploading it to the backend.
                        Buttons are provided that allow the user to insert sample JSON data (i.e. data that was provided in the task description).
                        Buttons are also provided that allow the user to insert data for block bookings and for multiple block bookings assigned to different guests and different hotels).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Combine single bookings into a continuous rate period. <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle completed"></span>
                <ul>
                    <li>The system allows data in single booking format or multiple block booking format.
                        When displaying these on the UI, all bookings are combined into a block period booking based on the rate, then hotel and then guest.
                        The UI will display all continuous bookings for a guest that is staying in a hotel for all nights that have the same rate.</li>
                    <li><U>NOTE:</U> For the combined data that was provided in the task description, this application combines the data based on a reservation start date (i.e. check-in date) and reservation end date (i.e. check-out date).
                        Therefore the combined booking data will differ slightly based on the end date.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Generate a unique color to associate with each rate. <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle completed"></span>
                <ul>
                    <li>The rate is used as a seed to a random colour. Therefore, the same rate will always return the same random colour.
                        No colours are saved or stored on the system as each are generated based on the rate value.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>The generated colors do need to be visually distinguishable. <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok-circle completed"></span>
                <ul>
                    <li>This is achieved by providing another random colour (also based on the seed but with an offset) to be used as a border around the reservation colour.
                        This will allow to similar colours that could potentially sit beside each other to be distinguishable.
                        Other ways that this could be done is by using different shadings, allowing the user to add custom icons or by using different shapes, etc..
                        but using another random colour as a border seemed to be the best approach as the chances are that these will always be distinguishable from close colours.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

